Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
selectPtnPinGuide(25.10)                              selectPtnPinGuide(25.10)

Name
       selectPtnPinGuide  - Selects a partition pin guide and highlights it in
       the design display window

Syntax
       selectPtnPinGuide

       [-help]

       <x1 y1 x2 y2>

       <pinGuideName>

       <metalLayer>

       <minSpace>

       [<pinGroupCell>]

       Selects a partition pin guide and highlights it in the  design  display
       window.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each selectPtnPinGuide parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command: man selectPtnPinGuide

       <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies the coordinates of the pin guide (x1 y1 x2 y2).

              Data_type: box, required

       <metalLayer>
              Specifies the layer on which the pin guide resides.

              Data_type: string, required

       <minSpace>
              Specifies the minimum pin spacing for the pin guide.

              Data_type: int, required

       <pinGroupCell>
              Specifies  the  cell  name if the pin guide is associated with a
              cell pin group.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <pinGuideName>
              Specifies the name of the pin guide.

              Data_type: string, required

Related Information
              * createPinGuide

              * deletePinGuide

              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

